  "text": "Different from the single-period bank financing problem with only single optimal solution, it can be seen from Theorem 2 that the retailer's optimal strategy is characterized by two threshold values, which divide the ordering decision space into three regions to guide financing, operational, and investment decisions. Similarly, the supplier equilibrium under single-period supplier financing can be drawn by the discussion of retailer's three initial inventory discount regions as THEOREM 4: w into Equation [CITATION_1] and derive the supplier's end-of-term profit function from w, we have:",
